assemblage.p:
The equation for a hyperbola centered at (h,k) has one of the two standard forms:
        \blert{\frac{(x-h)^2}{a^2} - \frac{(y-k)^2}{b^2} = 1}
            \blert{\frac{(y-k)^2}{b^2} - \frac{(x-h)^2}{a^2} = 1}

